text:
Algorithms give us what we want. 

Not what we SAY we want, but what our behaviors SHOW that we want. 

The algorithm is merely a mirror - if you don't like who is staring back, it's on you. http://flip.it/8fF6u9  via @flipboard and @shellypalmer
author: ikepigott

text:
Also - when Facebook's algorithm serves you up my latest photo, it might be within a few minutes, or you might be in the second wave after enough other people have engaged.

Live video is live. The vast majority of your timeline is not. There is no extra time for curation.
author: ikepigott

text:
I have wondered the same.

Algorithms are doing much better with still photos - but the challenge in trying to parse shapes and movements at 30 or 60 frames per second is daunting.
